      <hedline>
        <hl1>NO STOCK OFFERING FOR CHINA STEELMAKER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Shanghai Baosteel Group to issue $240-million in corporate bonds in lieu of stock market listing outside China (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China's largest steel producer, the Shanghai Baosteel Group, will issue $240 million in corporate bonds in lieu of an overseas stock market listing. In April, the company postponed the sale of its shares abroad because of poor market conditions. It said it still planned to list its shares overseas but would wait for the market climate to improve.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith (NYT)</p>
      </block>
